10/06/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Albania and BiH signed an agreement Monday (9 June) on the transportation of goods and people. Officials also signed a memorandum of understanding within the framework of the European integration process. Albanian Foreign Minister Ilir Meta said bilateral agreements protecting investments and abolishing double taxation would be signed next month in Tirana.
In other news Monday, Meta called for the inclusion of Kosovo in regional initiatives. Speaking at the Southeast Europe Co-operation Process summit in Sarajevo, Meta said Kosovo could be integrated into Europe only if it participates in regional programmes. (ATA, Albanian TV, BBC, Bosnian news agency, Onasa - 09/06/03)
